{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/2268/comments/17944987.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/diff/peter_mitrano/gazebo:3788afeb78e3..5bf694d6b331?path=gazebo%2Fcommon%2FCMakeLists.txt"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2268/_/diff#comment-17944987"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 2268, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/2268.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2268"}}, "title": "Add basic support for gnu precompiled headers"}, "content": {"raw": "I think these double `ifs` can be reduce to:\n\n\n```\n#!c++\n\nif (USE_PCH)\n    set(MORE_FLAGS \"-pthread\")\n    add_pch(gazebo_common common_pch.hh ${MORE_FLAGS})\nendif()\n```\n\nWe can expand this if statement when (or if) we enable PCH on OSX and Windows.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I think these double <code>ifs</code> can be reduce to:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">USE_PCH</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">MORE_FLAGS</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;-pthread&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">add_pch</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">gazebo_common</span> <span class=\"n\">common_pch</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">hh</span> <span class=\"err\">$</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">MORE_FLAGS</span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n<span class=\"n\">endif</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>We can expand this if statement when (or if) we enable PCH on OSX and Windows.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-04-29T14:32:28.100927+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "ht